<Concepts>
<Concept id="Monorepo_Architecture" label="Monorepo Architecture" description="A single, unified repository (ApexSigmaProjects.Dev) containing distinct directories for services/, agents/, libs/, docs/, _archive/, and scripts/. Centralizes development, simplifies dependency management, and enables automated dogfooding."/>
<Concept id="Unified_Dev_Environment" label="Unified Dev Environment" description="The strategy of using a single, root-level docker-compose.yml to launch, network, and manage the entire ecosystem of services for local development, coordinated from a single .code-workspace file."/>
<Concept id="Three_Layer_Architecture" label="Three-Layer Architecture (Tools, Workers, Orchestrator)" description="The strategic architectural model for the evolved memOS.as ecosystem. It consists of a 'Tools' layer (the core memOS API), a 'Workers' layer (a new agent swarm for intelligence), and an 'Orchestrator' layer (Dagster) to manage the data assets and workflows between them."/>
<Concept id="Dogfooding_Principle" label="Dogfooding Principle" description="A development methodology established for the memOS.as project, mandating that the core implementation team must be the first and primary users of the service to ensure its real-world viability and quality."/>
</Concepts>
<Tasks>
<Task id="memOS_Upgrade_P0" project="memOS.as" priority="Critical" description="Execute Phase 0 of the memOS Upgrade: Monorepo Integration. Task 1: Create the root-level docker-compose.yml for the unified development environment. Task 2: Scaffold and populate the libs/apexsigma-core shared library."/>
<Task id="AgentRegistry_Refactor" project="DevEnviro.as" priority="Critical" description="Refactor the AgentRegistry to be the single source of truth for live agent objects. Remove the reconstruction of AgentPersona from DB records and implement an in-memory registry with persistence hooks."/>
<Task id="POML_Engine_Phase1_Dev" project="poml-processor" priority="Critical" description="Begin POML Engine Phase 1: create Python package scaffold, add Dagster repository files, and implement the core parser pipeline using Tree-sitter and AST-grep for POML translation."/>
<Task id="Ingest_LLM_Path_Fix" project="InGest-LLM.as" priority="High" description="Modify the Dockerfile CMD/entrypoint to execute within the Poetry virtual environment (e.g., 'poetry run python -m ingest_llm.main') to resolve the container startup failure."/>
<Task id="tools_as_API_Deploy" project="tools.as" priority="High" description="Deploy the tools.as API service to enable the tool registry endpoints, allowing agents to discover and call memOS-backed tools."/>
<Task id="memos_Repo_Investigation" project="memOS.as" priority="Medium" description="Investigate the root cause of the structural deficiencies (missing README.md and package directory) in the 'memos.as' GitHub repository."/>
<Task id="memos_Backup_Cleanup" project="Ecosystem-Wide" priority="Low" description="Make a final decision on whether to keep or delete the 'services/memos.as.bak' backup directory."/>
</Tasks>
<Incidents>
<Incident id="incident_Implementation_Discrepancy">
<Timestamp>2025-09-13T21:00:00Z</Timestamp>
<Summary>A comprehensive audit revealed a critical 43% discrepancy between documented achievements and the actual implementation state.</Summary>
<Priority>CRITICAL</Priority>
<Status>Active</Status>
<Resolution>The "Operation Asgard Rebirth" umbrella initiative was created to address all identified gaps. The underlying issue remains unresolved until all sub-operations are complete.</Resolution>
</Incident>
<Incident id="incident_Poetry_Stabilization_Failure">
<Timestamp>2025-09-14T00:50:00Z</Timestamp>
<Summary>A multi-hour effort to stabilize service environments with Poetry was blocked by a misconfigured 'pyproject.toml' in the 'memos.as' service, which referenced a non-existent README and was missing its core package directory.</Summary>
<Priority>CRITICAL</Priority>
<Status>Resolved</Status>
<Resolution>The problematic 'memos.as' directory was backed up and a fresh copy was cloned from GitHub. The missing 'README.md' and 'memos/__init__.py' files were then manually created, which finally allowed 'poetry install' to succeed, stabilizing all service environments.</Resolution>
</Incident>
<Incident id="incident_Chaotic_Directory_Structure">
<Timestamp>2025-09-13T22:15:00Z</Timestamp>
<Summary>A messy, unstructured project directory was identified as a key organizational blocker, preventing efficient development, dependency management, and CI/CD automation.</Summary>
<Priority>CRITICAL</Priority>
<Status>Resolved</Status>
<Resolution>"Operation: Monorepo Genesis" was successfully executed on 2025-09-14, migrating the entire ecosystem into a clean monorepo architecture and establishing a new, stable baseline.</Resolution>
</Incident>
<Incident id="incident_AgentPersona_Flaw">
<Timestamp>2025-08-20T21:12:00Z</Timestamp>
<Summary>A critical architectural flaw in DevEnviro.as was identified: AgentPersona objects are inefficiently and incorrectly reconstructed from database records instead of using live, in-memory instances, leading to runtime inconsistency.</Summary>
<Priority>CRITICAL</Priority>
<Status>Active</Status>
<Resolution>A critical-priority task (AgentRegistry_Refactor) has been created to refactor the AgentRegistry to be the single source of truth for live agent objects and implement in-memory management with persistence hooks.</Resolution>
</Incident>
<Incident id="incident_Gemini_CLI_Listener_Restart_Loop">
<Timestamp>2025-09-12T23:45:00Z</Timestamp>
<Summary>The DevEnviro Gemini CLI Listener container is stuck in a restart loop, preventing any agent-based interactions with the core orchestrator.</Summary>
<Priority>High</Priority>
<Status>Active</Status>
<Resolution>No resolution has been planned yet. The issue needs to be investigated by analyzing container logs.</Resolution>
</Incident>
</KnowledgeBase>
<KnowledgeBase>
<Topic label="Strategic Operations">
<Description>High-level strategic plans governing the evolution of the ApexSigma ecosystem.</Description>
<Node id="Operation_Asgard_Rebirth" label="Operation Asgard Rebirth: Implementation & Correction">
<Detail>
<Summary>An umbrella operation focused on closing the critical implementation gaps identified in the verification report. It encompasses all corrective actions, including the 'Monorepo Genesis' and 'memOS Upgrade' operations.</Summary>
</Detail>
</Node>
<Node id="Operation_Monorepo_Genesis" label="Operation: Monorepo Genesis">
<Detail>
<Summary>A focused operation, completed on 2025-09-14, that resolved the chaotic project directory structure by migrating all code and artifacts into a structured monorepo. It was governed by the TPGP and MAR protocols and included a "Safe-Delete" workflow.</Summary>
</Detail>
</Node>
<Node id="Operation_memOS_Upgrade" label="Operation: memOS Upgrade">
<Detail>
<Summary>A focused, multi-phase operation to upgrade the memOS.as service. The plan was refined to include a 'Phase 0: Monorepo Integration' to leverage the new unified development environment before proceeding to the core service upgrade (Phase 1), orchestrator integration (Phase 2), and intelligence layer deployment (Phase 3).</Summary>
</Detail>
</Node>
</Topic>
<Topic label="Governance & Protocols">
<Description>The immutable laws and protocols that govern the ecosystem's development and operation.</Description>
<Node id="TPGP" label="TaskMaster Generation Protocol (TPGP)">
<Detail>
<Summary>The standard for creating all task plans. It mandates dual-output (Markdown for humans, POML for machines), per-task MAR roles (Implementer, Reviewer), explicit 'Done means Done' criteria, and a sequential workflow handoff protocol where the Reviewer's sign-off is the trigger for continuation.</Summary>
</Detail>
</Node>
<Node id="MAR_Protocol" label="MAR (Mandatory Agent Review) Protocol">
<Detail>
<Summary>A formal, mandatory quality gatekeeper workflow where a designated Reviewer agent must formally approve an Implementer agent's work on a task before the project can proceed. It is a core component of our multi-agent collaboration framework.</Summary>
</Detail>
</Node>
<Node id="Safe_Delete_Protocol" label="Safe-Delete Protocol">
<Detail>
<Summary>A workflow to prevent accidental data loss. Instead of permanent deletion, the `rm` and `del` commands are overridden by shell functions to move files to a temporary `_archive/trash` directory, from which they can be recovered or permanently deleted later.</Summary>
<CodeSnippet language="bash">
<![CDATA[
# Overrides the 'rm' command to move files to the workspace archive.
rm() {
    local TRASH_DIR="/path/to/your/ApexSigmaProjects.Dev/_archive/trash"
    mkdir -p "$TRASH_DIR"
    if [ "$#" -eq 0 ]; then
        command rm
        return
    fi
    for target in "$@"; do
        mv -v "$target" "$TRASH_DIR"
    done
}
]]>
</CodeSnippet>
</Detail>
</Node>
</Topic>
